The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, March 04, 2004 				 Inventions of Dance
																								The Biwakei dance company of Japan, founded in 1989 under the leadership of Setsuko Yamada, seeks to explore nuances and develop innovations in contemporary Japanese dance. A professor in the department of performing arts at the Kyoto University of Art and Design, Yamada has evolved a unique dance style over the years. Evoking delicate forms and fertile images, her works have received the highest critical acclaim the world over. Treasuring developed rhythms and transforming images in its exploration of the modern Japanese dance, the Biwakei dance companys innovations are best experienced in Yamadas own performances as well as in solo and group numbers by the troupe members. The word Biwa, meaning a fruit that is both toxic and yet possessing healing properties, underlines the companys ideal  a desire to build a creative space that serves as a source of positive inspiration and energy.																								Event: Contemporary Japanese dance																								When: Today at 6.30 pm																								Where: G.D. Birla Sabhagar
